    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-27T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-27T12:00:00-05:00" n="817"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d817">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.733/163: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-27T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >May 27, 1944—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received May 28—2:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>965. For De Wolf<note n="19" xml:id="d817fn19">Francis C. de Wolf, Chief,
                        Telecommunications Division.</note> from Otterman.<note n="20"
                        xml:id="d817fn20">Harvey B. Otterman, Assistant Chief, Telecommunications
                        Division.</note> Minister Posts and Telegraphs<note n="21" xml:id="d817fn21"
                        >Alirio Gómez Picón.</note> and our delegation have arrived at complete
                    agreement more satisfactory than our telegram May 23.<note n="22"
                        xml:id="d817fn22">Telegram 935, not printed.</note> It will be confirmed by
                    exchange of notes between Embassy and Colombian Foreign Minister<note n="23"
                        xml:id="d817fn23">Carlos Lozano y Lozano.</note> probably Monday.<note
                        n="24" xml:id="d817fn24">The agreement was signed on May 31, 1944, but was
                        not put into effect; see third paragraph of despatch 4426, September 13,
                        from Bogotá, <ref target="#pg_860">p. 860</ref>.</note> Embassy will advise
                    when notes signed. Text of note follows:</p>
                <p>[Here follows text of note to be exchanged with Colombian Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs, not printed.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed> [Otterman] <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Daniels</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
